BT 1 0 0 1 0 51 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (The ~2.3x calm/stressed coherence ratio is a ) Tj /F2 9 Tf (noise-averaged critical constant) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( -- not the ratio expected from the) Tj T* (deterministic formula \(which would give ~6x\), but the ratio that emerges from the log-normal distribution of gamma in the) Tj T* (simulation. This paper derives the exact value 2.3 from the noise-averaging integral over the log-normal distribution,) Tj T* (identifies it as the ratio \(gamma_stress/gamma_calm\)^0.5 x correction factor arising from the 3D Ising susceptibility) Tj T* (exponent, and names it the ) Tj /F2 9 Tf (Wike Coherence Contrast) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( \(WCC\).) Tj T* ET
